==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|vīlificāre|lang=la}}, present active infinitive of {{term|vīlificō||villify|lang=la}},

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈvɪl.ɪ.faɪ/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-vilify.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|vilif|ies}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To say [[defamatory]] things about someone or something.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[belittle]] through speech; to [[put down]].

